In morals, exemplary; In doctrine, uncorrupt; In reasoning, profound; In declaring Gods counsel, Perspicuous and solemn; And in death, peaceful.\""},"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":3,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"marriage","header":"Two siblings married two siblings — one ceremony","body":"On November 9, 1768 in Farmington, Cyprian Strong married Sarah Bull, and his sister Elizabeth Strong married Sarah's brother Martin Bull — both weddings on the same day. Two Strong siblings and two Bull siblings, bound together in a single ceremony.","number":1},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"His gravestone counts 44 years of ministry","body":"He was ordained at Chatham (now Portland) on August 9, 1767 and remained its Congregational pastor until his death on November 17, 1811 — 44 years in the same pulpit. His gravestone records both: \"In the 68th year of his age, And 44th of his ministry; In morals, exemplary; In doctrine, uncorrupt; In reasoning, profound.\""},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Yale or Harvard? — the record says Yale","body":"EH, the Strong family book, and Yale archival records all confirm he graduated Yale 1763. The Native Northeast Portal biography states Harvard — this appears to be an error in that source. He served as Farmington Town Clerk 1764-67 immediately after graduation, before ordination."},{"number":4,"category":"legacy","header":"His granddaughter walked the Trail of Tears","body":"His daughter Sarah Strong married Judge John Ellsworth; their daughter Harriet Ellsworth married Ainsworth Blunt at Brainerd Mission, Tennessee, where they ministered to the Cherokees. When the forced removal came in 1838, Blunt accompanied the Cherokees on the Trail of Tears before illness forced him back from the Mississippi. He later became the first mayor of Dalton, Georgia."}],"education":[{"degree":"B.A.","notes":"EH, Strong family book (5345-8), and Yale archival collection all confirm Yale 1763. Native Northeast Portal biography states Harvard — this appears to be an error in that source. Sprague Annals of the American Pulpit vol. I pp. 651-3 contains a life sketch.","school_name":"Yale College","graduation_year":1763,"institution_id":"INST022"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Cyprian Strong","first_name":"Cyprian","last_name":"Strong","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://images.findagrave.com/photos/2016/99/18878632_1460208376.jpg?size=photos250"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1763"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"cyprian-strong-1743"},"X00134":{"id":"X00134","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1748,"month":10,"day":17,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1785,"month":9,"day":14,"city":"Portland","county":"Middlesex","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States","cause":"sudden death"},"cross_connections":[],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":2,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00299","date_year":1768,"date_month":11,"date_day":9,"location_city":"Farmington","location_county":"Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1785,"children_ids":["H00669","H00670","H00671","H00672","H00673","H00674","H00675","H00676"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"I00137","date_year":1717,"date_month":8,"date_day":12,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1719,"children_ids":[]}],"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"marriage","header":"Two siblings married two siblings — one ceremony","body":"On November 9, 1768 in Farmington, Cyprian Strong married Sarah Bull, and his sister Elizabeth Strong married Sarah's brother Martin Bull — both weddings on the same day. Two Strong siblings and two Bull siblings, bound together in a single ceremony.","number":1}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM108"},"bio":{"display_name":"Sarah Bull","first_name":"Sarah","last_name":"Strong","maiden_name":"Bull","married_names":["Strong"]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"sarah-bull-1748"},"I00055":{"id":"I00055","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1702,"month":10,"day":8,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1751,"month":3,"day":30,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut"},"parents":{"mother_research_notes":"Margaret Hart — daughter of Capt. Thomas Hart (X00031), son of Stephen Hart (X00034)","father_research_notes":"Asahel Strong Sr. (b. Nov 14, 1668 Northampton MA) — married Margaret Hart, daughter of Capt. Thomas Hart (X00031)"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"H00103","children_ids":["H00293","H00294","H00295","H00296","H00297","H00298","H00299","H00300"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1729,"date_month":1,"date_day":8}],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 103"}],"gender":"male","tags":[],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[],"notable_blurb":null,"primary_url":null,"primary_url_label":null},"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"I00900","display_label":"Both Strong men who married Hooker descendants, 84 years apart","link_text":"Judge Elisha Beebe Strong"}],"bio":{"title":"Captain","display_name":"Captain Asahel Strong Jr.","first_name":"Asahel","last_name":"Strong","suffix":"Jr.","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"His Hooker marriage echoed down two more generations","body":"When Captain Asahel Strong Jr. married Sarah Hooker in 1729 at Farmington, Connecticut — a great-great-granddaughter of Rev. Thomas Hooker — he began a pattern that would echo through generations: their great-great-grandson Asahel Hooker Strong was born in 1776 with 'Hooker' preserved as his middle name, and 84 years after the first marriage, Judge Elisha Beebe Strong married another Thomas Hooker descendant, Dolly Goodwin Hooker, at Canandaigua, New York in 1813. By 1866, that second union had produced Beebe Hooker Strong of Milwaukee, the fourth person in the Strong family to carry the Hooker name — connecting the original Farmington parsonage to the Wisconsin frontier across 137 years."}],"slug":"asahel-strong-jr-1702"},"H00103":{"id":"H00103","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":4,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1708,"month":4,"day":16,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1777,"month":9,"day":18,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00030","mother_id":"I00031"},"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 103"},{"short":"Native Northeast Portal","url":"https://www.nativenortheastportal.com/bio/bibliography/hooker-ruth-1708-1777"}],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I00055","children_ids":["H00293","H00294","H00295","H00296","H00297","H00298","H00299","H00300"],"marriage_number":1,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1751,"date_year":1729,"date_month":1,"date_day":8},{"children_ids":[],"spouse_id":"I00134","marriage_number":2,"date_year":1772,"date_month":11,"date_day":19}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"H00795","display_label":"Hooker women who married Strongs in 1729 and 1813","link_text":"Dolly Goodwin Hooker"}],"gender":"female","narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Eight children with Capt. Asahel Strong Jr.","body":"She married Capt. Asahel Strong Jr. on January 8, 1729 and bore him eight children — including Rev. Cyprian Strong of Chatham. Asahel was a grandson of Stephen Hart through his mother Margaret Hart, closing another loop in the Hart-Hooker network."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Lost three children in September 1736","body":"In a single ten-day span — September 6 to 15, 1736 — three of her young children died: Lois and Ruth on the same day, then Elnathan nine days later. The cluster strongly suggests an epidemic moving through Farmington."},{"number":3,"category":"marriage","header":"Second husband Solomon Whitman lived to 93","body":"After Capt. Asahel Strong's death she married Solomon Whitman, who was Town Clerk at 92 and made a pair of shoes on his 90th birthday. He died at 93 from over-fatigue settling a fence dispute between two brothers."}],"number_of_marriages":2,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"bio":{"display_name":"Ruth Hooker Whitman","first_name":"Ruth","last_name":"Whitman","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":["Strong","Whitman"]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"ruth-whitman-1708"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}